description: Identifies which device created the packet
the length of the packet (not including all characters up-to the comma which follows this number)
the valid time for this packet (usually 1 second behind actual time)
indication of whether the CRIO is successfully synchronised to PTP time ( 1 = synced, 0 = not-synced )
equals the internal bench temperature (degC) of the device
indicates the flight number for this packet ( an "empty" string here indicates that the CRIO hasn't been assigned a flight number )
Reading in signed engineering unit (ppb) for Ozone Signal
Bench temperature (degC) used in instrument calculations (temperature compensation is on)
Absorption cell pressure reading (mmHg) used in instrument calculation (pressure compensation on)
Sample flow in cell A (L per min)
Sample flow in cell B (L per min)
